    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline">WHEN: INFO: WHEN:&#xD;&#xA;INFO: Watch it at str.sg/JhND</span>
    </section>

    <p>An In­ti­mate Per­for­mance With Amni Mus­fi­rah</p>
    <p>The Sin­ga­pore-born pro­ducer and singer-song­writer will be per­form­ing the songs she has writ­ten about fe­male em­pow­er­ment and shar­ing the sto­ries be­hind them. Amni has re­leased six sin­gles and is work­ing on her de­but al­bum, which is slated for re­lease next year. Part of Red Dot Au­gust, a cel­e­bra­tion of things uniquely Sin­ga­pore by the Es­planade.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Sun, 8pm - Sept 7, noon</p>
    <p>INFO: Watch it at str.sg/JhNR</p>
    <p>Mu­sic For The Soul – Be­yond Sec­ond Chances</p>
    <p>In­tune Mu­sic, founded by pi­anist Peng Chi Seng and vo­cal­ist Aaron Matthew Lim, has con­ducted mu­sic and per­for­mance lessons for Changi Prison in­mates since 2014. They founded the Yel­low Rib­bon PAC Alumni in the hope that through these reg­u­lar mu­sic jam­ming ses­sions and per­for­mance op­por­tu­ni­ties, the for­mer in­mates can stay grounded and find self-be­lief after their re­lease. The video con­sists of per­for­mances by In­tune Mu­sic and the Yel­low Rib­bon PAC Alumni. Part of Red Dot Au­gust, a cel­e­bra­tion of things uniquely Sin­ga­pore by the Es­planade.</p>
    <p>Wed, 8pm - Sept 7, noon Watch it at str.sg/JhNa</p>
    <p>Jass@Home: Swing­ing In Sin­ga­pore – A Cel­e­bra­tion Of Sin­ga­pore’s 55th Birthday</p>
    <p>Pre­sented by the Jazz As­so­ci­a­tion (Sin­ga­pore) (JASS), this per­for­mance fea­tures jazz ren­di­tions of Sin­ga­pore and Asean songs and orig­i­nal lo­cal com­po­si­tions, in­clud­ing the world pre­miere of The Lion Roars Again by Jass as­so­ciate direc­tor Weix­i­ang Tan. Home-grown vo­cal­ists Ale­may Fer­nan­dez, Rudy Djoe and New York-based Melissa Tham will also make ap­pear­ances. The video will be avail­able on the group’s Face­book and YouTube chan­nels.</p>
    <p>Aug 23, 8pm</p>


